			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Chain Mezzing Casters!<a name="53203"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 9:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Howdy Folks!
<br />

<br />
Wiladancer from Torv here. I have been doing tons of LDoN's lately (oh there's a shocker) and have found that the best means of disrupting casters can often be in chain-mezzing with Dreams of Terris (yes, I'm only lvl 64). However, certain questions have been posed to me about this and I figured I'd lay them out here for discussion and advice.
<br />

<br />
- Does Dreams of Terris have a Mem Blur effect? I do not notice any Mem Blur, to be honest, but can someone confirm.
<br />

<br />
- So long as the Melees know to follow the pull effect of the mez, you can really do some significant damage to the caster mobs. The caster mobs typically try to cast something once mez breaks, opening up a nice window of beatings from the tanks and you can typically get another mez on them, barring resists, prior to them getting a spell off. I've noticed a HUGE difference in take down time.
<br />

<br />
- Gating Mobs are no longer and issue as they cannot regain concentration and continue casting.
<br />

<br />
- My monk friend I group with 90% of the time has one heck of a push effect. I am wondering if I should stand behind him and Melee whilst I chain mez? My hope being his push would offset my pull.
<br />

<br />
Your thoughts and recommendations are always a blessing. Thank you.
<br />

<br />
Wila....</span></td>
