				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chain Mezzing Casters!<a name="53225"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 10:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I use the chain-mezz method a lot (along with bellow...if the mob is low enough for the stun component to work) to prevent CHeal/Gate.  I'll use it (chain-mezz) sometimes even if we have a Pally stunning.  Sometimes the Pally's timing may be off or something and having that extra chance of interupt is nice.  It's more of an added insurance type of thing.
<br />

<br />
Occasionally, I'll see a &quot;WTF?!?&quot; type of reaction on a chain-mezz, but not too often.  Usually, when I do, it's a pet class wondering why their pet disengaged.  My NORMAL xp group gotten very used to me employing this tactic and know that they can just send their pet back in every few seconds when it disengages.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">-treeb<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308563">(Tree)ble Clef</a><br>-------<br>"Music should strike fire from the heart of man, and bring tears from the eyes of woman."  -Ludwig van Beethoven</span></td>
