				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chain Mezzing Casters!<a name="53226"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 10:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I use it, or try to use it, in between pulls and against gating mobs. Which means Ill be doing a normal melee twist(with PoV). When the mob gets in CH or gate range hp wise, I switch to chain mezzing.
<br />

<br />
I general dont use it constantly during a fight. Only for gating and CHing. The reason, for me, is that most of the mobs spells will get resisted with PoV anyway and the added haste will get it dead quicker than me chain mezzing it. But gating mobs suck and so does CH, especially when a named does it(the ones you cant mezz).
<br />

<br />
For bards, the only better way to interrupt casters is with BB AA, but thats on an 18 sec refresh so not sustainable.
<br />

<br />
I rarely hear &quot;WTF??&quot; from group members, when I was using a mezz with a push affect I always let them know I'll be chain mezzing so they don't get confused and I constantly turn my char around so that I push both ways to keep the mob in a general area. With Lullaby I don't even bother anouncing chain mezzing anymore.
<br />

<br />
Good call on the 58 and 60 mezz with mem-wipe, I neglected looking those up.</span></td>
