				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chain Mezzing Casters!<a name="53293"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 5:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'll ring in as another bard that occationally uses mez to interupt spells.  SSoP (saryns) can also interupt spells, some have said it never works for them, but it has for me.  However, especially if you have pet classes in your group you might want to consider not doing a full chain-mez, because each mez means their pets back off and reduce DPS drastically.  As some said, keep it for gaters/healers, unless you don't have a good resist song yet (I know you do at level 64, but not every bard reading this will).  Also another tactic you can use is chain the mez, BUT restart it right before it lands each time unless you see a &quot;starts casting&quot; message, in which case of course let the mez land.  This way pets stay in battle as much as possible, plus there is less than 3 seconds between the beginning of each mez, so you are more likely to catch the fast cast spells.  And be very very sure that your group knows what you are doing, if you haven't brought it up beforehand, say something as soon as you start the song, so they know whats going on
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
