				<td colspan="2"><span>I would propose one important addition to that - MOBs that are enchanters.
<br />

<br />
Pulled one of those flying monkeys in the Everfrost LDoN, and saw my resist message without reading what had been cast on me.
<br />

<br />
All the sudden our Monk (MT) was beating on our Ranger, and ranger boy was &quot;Hey! Hey! Get the lizard off me!&quot;
<br />

<br />
So the rest of the fight I kept switch-mezzing the monkey and the monk. The monkey also got off an enthrall, so we finished him with 4 of us. Could have been much uglier.
<br />

<br />
Another time was pulling in MMC LDoN - was at the doorway at the top of the stair (having pulled the sides of the door already) when the response I got to my pulling song as I backed up was an enthrall.
<br />

<br />
The female paladin in the group who had been an entertainer with her sharp wit queried, &quot;Well Mr Kitty, where is our prey?&quot; I replied, &quot;It's up here, I'm enthralled .. so bring your shield and your stuns.&quot; Again, with a decent group it got dealt with only one other enthrall.
<br />

<br />
So .... I make mezzing MOB enchanters a priority - they channel through some stuns (as mentioned earlier).
<br />

<br />
Trusong OneFaith</span></td>
