				<td colspan="2"><span>If everyone in your group has half a brain they would know what to do (finish the low mob off). I am one of those people who almost never announce things I do, like say when I HoS, Slow, leech etc. 
<br />
I call mezzes when they are important not to be broken. Once you see a mob CHealing itself or know it will try to gate, chainmezz it and usually your group should understand what you do and why.
<br />

<br />
Else I just do what bards do, some people might notice it, others won't, and probably wonder why its so easy ;)
<br />

<br />
If you someday have a &quot;fix group&quot; with that you group and hang out almost every day and everyone knows his roll and also knows what each other does and can do it gets much easier. Its all a matter of expirience and trust I think. 
<br />

